TITLE: Workers at UK's largest container port to join rail strikes
SUMMARY: Almost 2,000 workers at the U.K.’s biggest container port will launch an eight-day strike Sunday over a pay dispute

TITLE: Finland asks: Does a prime minister have a right to party?
SUMMARY: A leaked video that shows Finland’s 36-year-old prime minister dancing and singing with friends at a private party has triggered a debate among Finns about what level of reveling is appropriate for their leader

TITLE: Germany, US note 'courage' of jailed Russia critic Navalny
SUMMARY: On the second anniversary of the poison attack on Alexei Navalny, Germany and the United States have hailed the determination of the Kremlin critic who is imprisoned in Russia

TITLE: Mexico arrests ex-attorney general in missing students case
SUMMARY: Prosecutors in Mexico say they have arrested a former attorney general and issued warrants for 83 army soldiers and officers, police and gang members in the 2014 disappearance of 43 students

TITLE: Bus collision at accident site leaves 15 dead in Turkey
SUMMARY: Officials in southern Turkey say at least 15 people were killed when a passenger bus collided with emergency teams handling an earlier road accident

TITLE: Greece rid of budget watch but inflation, energy woes bite
SUMMARY: Greece's close financial oversight by European Union creditors is ending

TITLE: UN: US buying big Ukraine grain shipment for hungry regions
SUMMARY: The head of the World Food program says the United States is stepping up to buy about 150,000 metric tons of grain from Ukraine in the next few weeks for an upcoming shipment to hungry areas of the world

TITLE: Russian shelling, Ukrainian airstrike reflect broadening war
SUMMARY: Russian forces are stepping up their battle to seize one of the cities in eastern Ukraine not already under their control while continuing to fire on areas in the country’s north and south

TITLE: African migratory birds threatened by hot, dry weather
SUMMARY: Africa’s migratory birds are threatened by changing weather patterns in the center and east of the continent that have depleted natural water systems and caused a devastating drought

TITLE: Chinese farmers struggle as scorching drought wilts crops
SUMMARY: Scorching heat during China's driest summer in six decades has wilted crops and left farmers struggling

TITLE: Chemical tanker, cargo ship crash near southwestern Japan
SUMMARY: A Japanese chemical tanker ship has crashed into a cargo ship off the coast of southwestern Japan

TITLE: At least 10 killed as gunmen storm hotel in Somali capital
SUMMARY: Police and eyewitnesses say at least 10 people were killed in an attack by Islamic militants who stormed a hotel in Somalia’s capital late Friday

TITLE: Nicaraguan police detain bishop, other priests in raid
SUMMARY: Nicaraguan police have raided the residence of a Roman Catholic bishop, detaining him and several other people holed up inside for two weeks

TITLE: Montenegrin government falls over ties with Serbian Church
SUMMARY: The Montenegrin government has collapsed in a no-confidence vote that followed a rift over relations with the powerful Serbian Orthodox Church

TITLE: 'I lost everything': Algeria reels from deadly wildfires
SUMMARY: Algerian firefighters have extinguished all but one of over 50 wildfires that ravaged the country this week

TITLE: Russia's Gazprom to shut gas pipeline to Europe for 3 days
SUMMARY: Russia’s state-owned energy company Gazprom says a key pipeline conveying natural gas to Europe will shut down for three days at the end of this month to undergo “routine maintenance.”

TITLE: China jails Canadian tycoon for 13 years for finance crimes
SUMMARY: A court says Chinese-born Canadian tycoon who disappeared from Hong Kong in 2017 has been sentenced to 13 years in prison for a multibillion-dollar string of financial offenses and his company was fined $8.1 billion

TITLE: France's Macron assails Putin's 'brutal attack' on Ukraine
SUMMARY: French President Emmanuel Macron on Friday accused the Russian leader of launching a “brutal attack” on Ukraine in an imperialist, revanchist violation of national borders

TITLE: Palestinians: Israeli troops shot, killed man in West Bank
SUMMARY: A 58-year-old Palestinian man was shot and killed outside a bakery during an Israeli raid in the occupied West Bank

TITLE: Market blast in north Syria kills at least 9, injures dozens
SUMMARY: A Syrian opposition war monitor and a paramedic group say a rocket attack on a crowded market in a town held by Turkey-backed opposition fighters killed 15 people and wounded dozens

TITLE: Detained aide of Pakistan's former PM Imran Khan in hospital
SUMMARY: Pakistani officials say an aide of former Prime Minister Imran Khan who was recently arrested on treason charges for alleged anti-military remarks was hospitalized this week after complaining of breathing difficulties

TITLE: AP PHOTOS: Brazil slave descendants revive rites after COVID
SUMMARY: For three long years, Vandeli Matos was an emperor in waiting. The symbolic coronation of the 33-year-old finally occurred this week when the Kalunga quilombo — as Brazilian communities descended from runaway slaves are known — gathered for the first time since the pandemic began.

TITLE: Sweden: 2 wounded in shopping center shooting
SUMMARY: Swedish police say two people have been wounded in a shooting at a shopping center in the southern city of Malmo

TITLE: Russia's Gazprom says key pipeline conveying natural gas to Europe will shut down 3 days for 'routine maintenance'
SUMMARY: Russia's Gazprom says key pipeline conveying natural gas to Europe will shut down 3 days for 'routine maintenance'

TITLE: Roadside bombing kills 2 policemen in northwestern Pakistan
SUMMARY: Pakistani police say a remotely detonated roadside bomb killed two policemen in a former militant stronghold in the country's northwest
